releases/0/tender/description:
Mandeville School is a day primary school for boys and girls with severe learning difficulties some of whom have additional physical, medical and/or sensory disabilities and others who have autism. 
The School demands a high standard of cleanliness especially due to the numerous health issues from which our children suffer. This tender is for the provision of daily term-time cleaning services and three periodic deep cleans for a contractual duration of two years.

releases/0/tender/title: Cleaning Tender for Calday Grange Grammar School
releases/0/tender/description: This cleaning tender process is targeted to have a cleaning contract in place to commence on 01/01/18. The process will include the creation of a select bidder list following analysis of SQ documents (within which the scoring criteria will be included). The nature of the contract demands a good local infrastructure to provide and maintain the level and standard of cleaning and support required by the School management team. Labour resource and relief cover is very important. We have set a Minimum level of turnover for this tender at 250 000 GBP which takes into account the contract turnover and cash flow associations. In the SQ, this is a discretionary pass/fail question on the basis that we will consider any additional guarantees and formal assurances such as parent company guarantors or similar which must be included to support any submission

releases/0/tender/description:
The ACC Liverpool Group Limited is seeking to establish a contract for the provision of High Voltage control, operation and maintenance services. It is anticipated that the contract will commence on 30.12.2016 for a period of 5 years until 29.12.2021.

Please review the details in the attachments provided and, if your organisation wishes to express an interest in this procurement process, please email purchasing@accliverpool.com  as soon as possible.  

Details of the timelines associated with this procurement are contained in the attachment.

Additional information: Additional information:

Organisations should register their interest in this Tender by email to purchasing@accliverpool.com

Please note there is an optional group site visit scheduled for Wednesday 9th November 2016. Interested parties should indicate their availability and intention to attend in their Expression of Interest.

The ACC Liverpool Group will not be held responsible for lack of communication to any organisation who does not register their interest.

releases/0/tender/title: Consideration of a range of Market and Regulatory Frameworks to support future scenarios for the decarbonisation of the GB Gas Network
releases/0/tender/description:
The Department for Business, Energy & Industrial Strategy (BEIS) wishes to commission a project to consider a range of Market and Regulatory Frameworks that could support a repurposed or reconfigured GB gas network to deliver a total decarbonisation of heat. This project is an initial long-term futures piece to improve BEIS' understanding of the possible risks, uncertainties and other barriers that may arise in relation to market and regulatory frameworks if the GB gas network were to be repurposed or reconfigured to achieve 2050 decarbonisation objectives.
      
      For background information, the full specification and further information on this project please see the ITT.
